-- Banks OK $21.1 billion loans to Softbank for Sprint deal: sources
-- 
-- Mon Oct 15, 2012 4:31am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/15/us-sprint-softbank-banks-idUSBRE89E05N20121015

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Four banks approved loans totalling 1.65 trillion yen ($21.1 billion) to Softbank Corp, three sources with direct knowledge of the matter told Reuters on Monday, bringing the company closer to clinching a $20 billion deal to take control of U.S. carrier Sprint Nextel Corp. 
 Mizuho Financial Group Inc, Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group, Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group and Deutsche Bank will provide the loans to Softbank, the sources said. The four banks submitted a commitment letter to Softbank promising the loans on Monday, they said. (Reporting by  Mari Saito ; Editing by  Michael Watson )